<h1>Cook IRL — Technical Overview</h1>

<blockquote>
  <strong>AI-powered recipe extraction and management that bridges the gap between saving recipes, organizing and actually cooking them.</strong>
</blockquote>

<hr>

<h2>Tech Stack</h2>

<table>
  <tr><th>Layer</th><th>Technology</th></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Mobile</strong></td><td>Flutter 3.9+, Riverpod, GoRouter</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Backend</strong></td><td>Node.js 22, TypeScript, Express</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>AI/ML</strong></td><td>Google Gemini 2.5 Flash, Cloud Vision API, OpenAI Whisper</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Vector Search</strong></td><td>Pinecone (text-embedding-3-small, 512 dims)</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Database</strong></td><td>Firebase Firestore</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Infrastructure</strong></td><td>Firebase Functions, Cloud Run, Cloud Tasks</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Payments</strong></td><td>RevenueCat</td></tr>
</table>

<hr>

<h2>Architecture</h2>

<pre>
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                     Flutter Mobile App                            │
│         (Riverpod State Management + GoRouter Navigation)         │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                                │
                    ┌───────────┴───────────┐
                    ▼                       ▼
         ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐
         │ Firebase Auth    │    │ Cloud Run API    │
         │ Firestore        │    │ (Express.js)     │
         │ Cloud Storage    │    └────────┬─────────┘
         └──────────────────┘             │
                                          ▼
                              ┌──────────────────────┐
                              │   LangGraph Agent    │
                              │  (Recipe Extraction) │
                              └──────────┬───────────┘
                    ┌────────────────────┼────────────────────┐
                    ▼                    ▼                    ▼
            ┌─────────────┐      ┌─────────────┐      ┌─────────────┐
            │ Vision API  │      │ Gemini 2.5  │      │  Pinecone   │
            │ (OCR)       │      │ (Parsing)   │      │ (Search)    │
            └─────────────┘      └─────────────┘      └─────────────┘
</pre>

<hr>

<h2>Core Features</h2>

<h3>1. Universal Recipe Import</h3>

<p>Import recipes from <strong>any source</strong> with AI-powered extraction:</p>

<table>
  <tr><th>Source</th><th>How It Works</th></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>URL</strong></td><td>Paste any recipe link — Instagram, TikTok, YouTube, blogs — AI extracts structured data</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>PDF</strong></td><td>Upload cookbook PDFs or scanned recipe documents</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Photo Scan</strong></td><td>Snap a photo of a recipe card, magazine page, or handwritten note</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Video</strong></td><td>Extract recipes from cooking videos with native multimodal AI</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>iOS Share Extension</strong></td><td>Share directly from Safari, Instagram, TikTok — imports without leaving the app</td></tr>
</table>

<p><strong>AI Pipeline:</strong></p>
<pre>Input → LangGraph Router → [PDF|Image|Video|URL|Text] → Gemini 2.5 Flash → Structured Recipe</pre>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Images</strong>: Vision API (OCR + labels) → Gemini parsing</li>
  <li><strong>Videos</strong>: Native multimodal processing (frames + audio in single pass)</li>
  <li><strong>URLs</strong>: Web scraper + structured extraction</li>
  <li><strong>PDFs</strong>: pdf-parse + Vision API for scanned documents</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h3>2. Smart Recipe Search &amp; Discovery</h3>

<p><strong>Three powerful ways to find recipes:</strong></p>

<table>
  <tr><th>Mode</th><th>How It Works</th></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Text Search</strong></td><td>Natural language queries ("quick pasta under 30 mins")</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Voice Search</strong></td><td>Speak your query — Whisper transcribes, AI searches</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Ingredient Scan</strong></td><td>Scan items in your fridge — find recipes you can make now</td></tr>
</table>

<p><strong>Hybrid Search Engine:</strong></p>
<pre>// Vector embedding + metadata filters
const results = await pinecone.query({
  vector: embedding,  // text-embedding-3-small (512 dims)
  filter: { userId, categories: { $in: ["dinner"] }, cookTime: { $lte: 1800 } },
  topK: 20
});</pre>

<hr>

<h3>3. Cookbook Organization</h3>

<p><strong>Organize recipes your way:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Cookbooks</strong> — Group recipes into collections (Weeknight Dinners, Holiday Baking, etc.)</li>
  <li><strong>Categories &amp; Tags</strong> — Filter by cuisine, meal type, difficulty, dietary restrictions</li>
  <li><strong>Shared Cookbooks</strong> — Collaborate with family or friends on shared collections</li>
  <li><strong>Favorites</strong> — Quick access to your most-loved recipes</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h3>4. Tasks &amp; Smart Reminders</h3>

<p><strong>From recipe to reality:</strong></p>

<table>
  <tr><th>Feature</th><th>Description</th></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Task Lists</strong></td><td>Create shopping lists, meal prep tasks, cooking schedules</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Recipe Linking</strong></td><td>Attach tasks directly to recipes ("Buy ingredients for Lasagna")</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Subtasks</strong></td><td>Break down complex tasks with checkable subtasks</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Smart Reminders</strong></td><td>Push notifications at the right time — never forget to defrost</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Recurring Tasks</strong></td><td>Daily, weekly, or custom recurrence patterns</td></tr>
</table>

<p><strong>Server-Side Scheduler:</strong></p>
<pre>Scheduler (every 5 min) → Query due tasks → FCM Topic (user_&lt;uid&gt;) → Push notification</pre>

<p>Notification types: Shopping | Cooking | General</p>

<hr>

<h3>5. iOS Home Screen Widgets</h3>

<p><strong>Your recipes, always accessible:</strong></p>

<table>
  <tr><th>Widget</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Task Widget</strong></td><td>See today's cooking tasks at a glance</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Reminder Widget</strong></td><td>Upcoming reminders on your lock screen</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Recipe Widget</strong></td><td>Quick access to favorite recipes</td></tr>
</table>

<p>Built with <strong>WidgetKit</strong> — native iOS performance, background refresh, deep linking into the app.</p>

<hr>

<h3>6. Immersive Cooking Mode</h3>

<p><strong>Step-by-step guidance while cooking:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Animated Backgrounds</strong> — Custom GLSL shaders for each cooking method (bake, fry, simmer, grill...)</li>
  <li><strong>Built-in Timers</strong> — Per-step countdown timers with audio alerts</li>
  <li><strong>Hands-Free</strong> — Voice commands and audio readout of instructions</li>
  <li><strong>Keep Screen Awake</strong> — No more tapping with flour-covered fingers</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Data Models</h2>

<h3>Recipe</h3>
<pre>{
  id, name, userId,
  ingredients: Record&lt;string, { name, quantity, unit, category }&gt;,
  instructions: Record&lt;string, { text, timeType, timeInSeconds }&gt;,
  categories: ["dinner", "italian"],
  difficulty: "easy" | "medium" | "hard",
  prepTimeInSeconds, cookTimeInSeconds,
  images: Record&lt;string, { url, source }&gt;
}</pre>

<h3>Task (with Reminders)</h3>
<pre>{
  taskId, title, createdBy,
  label: "shopping" | "cook" | "general",
  subtasks: Record&lt;string, { title, completed }&gt;,
  reminder: { remindAt: timestamp, recurrence: "daily" | "weekly" },
  linkedRecipes: { recipes: string[], details: {...} }
}</pre>

<hr>

<h2>Mobile App</h2>

<p><strong>State Management:</strong> Riverpod 3.x with <code>DataResult&lt;T&gt;</code> pattern for loading states</p>

<p><strong>Navigation:</strong> GoRouter with <code>StatefulShellRoute</code> for bottom navigation</p>

<p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>iOS Share Extension for importing from any app</li>
  <li>Home Screen Widgets (WidgetKit) for task reminders</li>
  <li>Custom GLSL shaders for cooking step animations</li>
  <li>5-language localization (CSV-based)</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>RevenueCat Implementation</h2>

<h3>Mobile SDK Integration (Flutter)</h3>

<pre>// Fetch offerings (OfferingNotifier)
void fetchOfferings() async {
  final Offerings offerings = await Purchases.getOfferings();
  state = state.copyWith(data: offerings.current);
}

// Purchase flow (CurrentPackageNotifier)
Future&lt;void&gt; purchase(bool restore, Function() onCompleted) async {
  if (restore) {
    final info = await Purchases.restorePurchases();
    if (info.activeSubscriptions.isEmpty) {
      showToast("No active purchases found");
    }
    return;
  }

  final purchaseParams = PurchaseParams.package(selectedPackage);
  await Purchases.purchase(purchaseParams);
  onCompleted();
}</pre>

<h3>Entitlement Check</h3>

<pre>// Check if user has active Pro subscription
Package? get currentActiveUserPackage {
  return state.data?.availablePackages.firstWhere(
    (package) =&gt;
        currentUser?.activeSubscription?.productId == 
            package.storeProduct.identifier &amp;&amp;
        currentUser?.activeSubscription?.status == 'active',
  );
}

bool get isProUser =&gt; currentActiveUserPackage != null;</pre>

<h3>Server-Side Webhook</h3>

<pre>App Store → RevenueCat → POST /subscriptions/webhook → Firestore</pre>

<p><strong>Webhook Events Handled:</strong></p>
<pre>const PURCHASE_EVENTS = [
  "INITIAL_PURCHASE", 
  "RENEWAL", 
  "SUBSCRIPTION_EXTENDED", 
  "PRODUCT_CHANGE"
];

const CANCEL_EVENTS = [
  "UNSUBSCRIBE", 
  "EXPIRATION", 
  "BILLING_ERROR", 
  "BILLING_ISSUE"
];</pre>

<p><strong>Purchase Event Handler:</strong></p>
<pre>async handlePurchaseEvent(event, user) {
  const subscription = {
    id: event.transaction_id,
    productId: event.new_product_id ?? event.product_id,
    entitlements: event.entitlement_ids || [],
    promoCode: event.offer_code ?? null,
    durations: {
      startAt: event.purchased_at_ms,
      endAt: event.expiration_at_ms,
    },
    status: "active",
  };

  await userService.updateSubscription(user.id, subscription);
  
  if (event.offer_code) {
    await this.claimPromoCode(event.offer_code);
  }
  
  await this.createTransaction(event, user);
}</pre>

<h3>Subscription Data Model</h3>

<pre>// Stored in Firestore users/{uid}.activeSubscription
activeSubscription: {
  id: string,                    // transaction_id
  productId: string,             // e.g. "cookirl_pro_monthly"
  entitlements: string[],        // ["pro"]
  promoCode: string | null,      // offer code if used
  status: "active" | "cancelled" | "expired",
  durations: { 
    startAt: number,             // purchased_at_ms
    endAt: number                // expiration_at_ms
  },
  updatedAt: number
}</pre>

<h3>Transaction Records</h3>

<p>Each purchase creates a transaction record for analytics:</p>
<pre>// Stored in Firestore transactions/{id}
{
  id, transactionId,
  amount: { price, currency, type: "charge" },
  createdBy: { uid, name, email },
  meta: { subscriptionId, productId, durations }
}</pre>

